Besides his important perspectives on current political debates, his groundbreaking work has been informing several discussions in the history of cultural field. His work, "Los derechos del alma," offers an innovative approach to intellectual and legal polemics from 19th-century Latin America. By concentrating in the debates on natural law during that period, Rafael discusses a wide array of topics, such as slavery and abolitionism, the disputes between liberals and conservatives, political translation and constitutionalism, and the cultural genealogies of republicanism and liberalism.
